└──────────┬──────────┘
           │ REST API
           │ JWT Auth
           ↓
┌─────────────────────┐
│   FastAPI Backend   │
│  ├─ Auth            │
│  ├─ Profiles        │
│  ├─ AI Generation   │
│  └─ Validation      │
└──────────┬──────────┘
           │
    ┌──────┴──────┐
    ↓             ↓
┌────────┐   ┌──────────┐
│MongoDB │   │ Gemini   │
│Database│   │ API      │
└────────┘   └──────────┘


================================================================================
SECTION 4: COMPLETE FEATURES & IMPLEMENTATION
================================================================================

4.1 FEATURE 1: USER AUTHENTICATION

Registration Flow:
User → Email/Password/Name → Validation → bcrypt Hash → MongoDB Store
→ JWT Generated (24h) → Token to Frontend → localStorage

Implementation:
- POST /auth/register - Create user account
- POST /auth/login - Authenticate user
- POST /auth/refresh - Refresh expired token
- Password hashed with bcrypt (10 salt rounds)
- Tokens include user_id and expiration

Security:
- Never store plain passwords
- JWT signature verified on backend
- Token auto-refresh before expiration
- Logout clears localStorage


4.2 FEATURE 2: ONBOARDING (5-STEP PROCESS)

STEP 1: BASIC INFORMATION
Inputs: Name, Email, Age, Gender
Validation: All required, age 15-120
Output: Saved to form state

STEP 2: FITNESS PROFILE  
Inputs: Height (cm), Weight (kg), Fitness Level, Goal
Real-time: BMI calculation
Suggestion: Target weight for healthy BMI 22-24
Validation: Ranges checked

Formula: BMI = weight(kg) / (height(m))²
Target: BMI 22 (healthy middle range)
Display: Real-time color-coded feedback

STEP 3: HEALTH & PREFERENCES
Inputs:
• Location (text) - Used for regional cuisine
• Health Issues (multi-select) - Diabetes, BP, Heart, etc.
• Food Preference (optional) - "Vegetarian Only" checkbox
Default: If unchecked = 'mixed' (veg + non-veg)

STEP 4: CONFIRMATION
Display: All information in organized cards
Actions: [Edit] buttons to go back | [Confirm] to proceed
Validation: Content review only (no new input)

STEP 5: GENERATION
Processing:
1. Show "Generating Plans..." spinner
2. Call POST /ai/workout (with profile)
3. Call POST /ai/diet (with profile + location + food pref)
4. Gemini generates plans
5. Parse and validate responses
6. Save to MongoDB
7. Cache in Zustand store
8. Navigate to dashboard

Success: Plans ready for viewing on dashboard


4.3 FEATURE 3: AI WORKOUT PLAN GENERATION

Input: User fitness level, goal, age, height, weight, health conditions

Gemini Prompt Includes:
- Fitness level (affects exercise difficulty)
- Goal (affects exercise selection)
- Health conditions (exercises to avoid)
- Available time/days

Output: 7-day workout plan with:
- Exercise names
- Sets and reps
- Rest duration (seconds)
- Difficulty level
- Muscle groups targeted

Example Output:
Day 1: Full Body Strength (45 min)
- Push-ups: 3 sets x 15 reps, 60s rest
- Squats: 3 sets x 20 reps, 60s rest
- Plank: 3 sets x 30 sec hold, 60s rest

Storage: MongoDB workout_plans collection
Display: WorkoutPlanPage component


4.4 FEATURE 4: LOCATION-AWARE DIET PLANNING

KEY INNOVATION: Regional cuisine awareness

Location Examples:
- India: Dal, Paneer, Rice, Roti, Sambar, Idli, Salad
- USA: Chicken, Broccoli, Brown Rice, Fruits
- Mediterranean: Olive Oil, Feta, Vegetables, Fish
- East Asia: Rice, Tofu, Vegetables, Seafood

Gemini Instruction:
"Use local cuisine from [location]. Each meal must include:
- Meal type and time
- Dish name and description
- Calories and macros (protein, carbs, fats)
- Food type (veg/non-veg)
- EXACT QUANTITIES (not approximations)
  Example: Idli: 3 pieces, Sambar: 1 cup, Oil: 1 tsp"

Output Example:
Breakfast (8:00 AM): Idli with Sambar
Calories: 250 | Protein: 12g | Veg
Quantity:
• Idli: 3 pieces
• Sambar: 1 cup
• Chutney: 2 tbsp

Storage: MongoDB diet_plans collection
Display: 
- Dashboard (compact): Meal names only
- DietPlanPage (detailed): Full info + green quantity section


4.5 FEATURE 5: FOOD PREFERENCE MANAGEMENT

Selection in Onboarding:
Step 3: Single optional button "Vegetarian Only"
- If unchecked: food_preference = 'mixed'
- If checked: food_preference = 'veg'

Implementation:
State: formData.foodPreference
Sent to backend: food_preference field
Stored: user_profiles.food_preference

Gemini Integration:
"User food preference: Vegetarian Only" or "Mixed"
Affects meal suggestions immediately

Edit in Settings:
Display (read-only): "Mixed (Veg + Non-Veg)" or "Vegetarian Only"
Edit mode (dropdown):
- Mixed (Veg + Non-Veg)
- Vegetarian Only

Save Flow:
1. User selects new preference
2. Click Save
3. API: PUT /user/profile with food_preference
4. Backend updates database
5. Zustand store updates
6. Optional: Ask to regenerate plans
7. New plans will include only selected type


4.6 FEATURE 6: REAL-TIME BMI CALCULATOR

Formula:
BMI = weight(kg) / (height(m))²

Calculation:
heightInMeters = height / 100
bmi = weight / (heightInMeters * heightInMeters)

Categories:
< 18.5: Underweight ⚠️ (Yellow)
18.5-24.9: Normal ✓ (Green)
25-29.9: Overweight ⚠️ (Orange)
≥ 30: Obese ❌ (Red)

Target Weight:
Aims for BMI 22 (healthy middle)
targetWeight = 22 × (height in meters)²

Display:
"Your BMI: 26.2 (Overweight)"
"Your target weight: ~71 kg"
"Weight to lose: ~14 kg"

Updates: Real-time as user types height/weight


